FRED L. TICHENOR, RESPONDENT, v. HARTFORD ACCIDENT AND INDEMNITY COMPANY, APPELLANT. Submitted October 16, 1931 Decided January 20, 1932.

Before Justices Campbell, Lloyd and Bodine.

For the appellant, Quinn, Parsons & Doremus. For the respondent, Samuel Y. Hampton. Per Curiam.

Fo specification of determinations of the District Court with which the appellant is dissatisfied, as required by rule 145 of this court, is presented in the record brought before us in this case. There is, therefore, nothing before us for review.

The appeal is dismissed, with costs.
